== English == 
=== Etymology===
Humorous formation from [[dyslexia]] by metathesis as if due to dyslexia.

=== Noun===
'''lysdexia''' ''(uncountable)''
# ''(humorously)'' [[Dyslexia]].
# ''(informal)'' Being prone to [[metathesis]] in reading,  writing, or speech due to (real or imagined) [[dyslexia]].

===Related terms===
* [[lysdexic]]

